     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>In laudem Authoris.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>T<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>ough carping spight, should sit in <hi>Momus</hi> chaire▪</l>
      <l>And <hi>Zoylus</hi> fume, gnashing his venime lawes:</l>
      <l>Though <hi>Crittick Satires,</hi> raue and rend their haire,</l>
      <l>And <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>nuy threat mee, with his <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 word">
            <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
         </gap> pawes.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Yet this my pen, for <hi>Raynolds</hi> sake shall write,</l>
      <l>Whose nouell lines, vnfolds a fer<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>ill spring:</l>
      <l>Re<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>eales at large, sound loue in zelous plight,</l>
      <l>Inchac'd with wo, and warl<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>ke sonneting.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Delighfull Poems, ioyn'd with pleasant good,</l>
      <l>And harmelesse pleasure, mixt w<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>th loftie straines:</l>
      <l>Then <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>oule <hi>Thersites,</hi> cease thy rayling moode,</l>
      <l>And giue at least, good words for so much paines.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>But i<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap> abroad, thy enuy needs <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>ust flie,</l>
      <l>Despight not him, who seekes to pleasure thee.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>Abraham Sauere Gentleman.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
